song_name: Where Have You Been All My Life

version_description: INTRO riff included from other versions with capo placed on the 3rd fret for acoustic playing.
Only 2 acoustic chord versions listed: one under the Beatles the other under George Harrison. This is a different approach to either.

A number of tabs use Am/F#, Am6 of F#m7-5 instead od D9/F#. Since this is a tab for a single guitar some aspects of the complete arrangement must be taken into count, and therefore D9/F# sounds a bit better. Instead of playing Fmaj7 like it's described above there's a slightly more comfortable way to play it and it goes like this: Fmaj7 x 3 3 2 1 0 However, if you play it like this you'll no longer have the descending bass line (G-F#-F) on the 6th string.
The Beatles - Why - No Capo - Link https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xWRuoBKHabM.

song_name: World Is Waiting For The Sunrise

version_description: I have modified the chords in the verses to make them incorporate some harmony notes in vocals. (Much like the Dmaj7 chord in ’This Boy’)The previously submitted versions did not include the E/B chord in the line “For red is the colour that my baby wore ( As well as in the subsequent verses)as well as the G# chord over the first ’true’ in the closing sequence “Yes it is it’s true, yes it is it’s true ) The G# is included in version #1 but this version does not indicate it’s appearance as closing out the song -as another bridge follows it on that version.-I have also tabbed out the short guitar passage that closes the track after the vocals--not included in any previously-submitted version.
Simpler way to achieve right key, played in D with a capo. Full chord legend included.
